8.  Manuscript editor (international, 1.5 person–months, intermittent). The manuscript editor 
will edit the Key Indicators for Asia and the Pacific 2012, including the tables and charts in the 
publication, following the ADB Handbook of Style and Usage.1 The editing will include a number 
of editing rounds of the typeset version until a desired quality is achieved. The editor will also 
make suggestions regarding the layout, and carry out the following tasks:  
(i)  reorganize text so that the subject matter is easy to understand and is logically  
presented;  
(ii)  eliminate wordiness and repetition, and reduce ambiguity; 
(iii)  query discrepancies, possible typographical errors, and non-English terms; 
(iv)  edit tables and figures, and recast if required; 
(v)  ensure that subheadings are consistent and logical; 
(vi)  check references to tables, figures, appendixes, and parts of the text; 
(vii)  edit notes to ensure that the text references are correct; 
(viii)  edit reference lists; 
(ix)  edit the foreword and acknowledgment of Key Indicators for Asia and the Pacific 
2012; 
(x)  check final changes; 
(xi)  work closely with the Key Indicators overall coordinator; and 
(xii)  check and sign off on the layout.  

9.  Graphics designer (national, 1 person-month, intermittent). The graphics designer will 
be responsible for text  layout,  encoding  of corrections,  re-layout,  and formatting  of graphic 
elements of Key Indicators for Asia and the Pacific 2012, including refining the web version. The 
designer must be skilled in working with Creative Suite 4 (or 5), MS Word and Excel, and will 
prepare  InDesign,  Illustrator,  and  PDF  files  of  the  interiors  and  covers  using  the  original 
manuscripts submitted in MS Word and Excel. In particular, the graphics designer will: 
(i)  lay out Key Indicators for Asia and the Pacific 2012; 
(ii)  reformat tables and charts and encode corrections in the main text, based on 
corrections received from ERDI staff and consultants; 
(iii)  prepare the final layout for the publication; 
(iv)  encode final text and graphical corrections from ERDI staff and consultants; 
(v)  deliver the final artwork for the publication’s covers to ERDI for final offset printing; 
(vi)  deliver the web-ready and pre-flight consolidated PDF of the publication to ERDI; 
and 
(vii)  perform other related tasks as assigned by ERDI.  





